AWKA – The Executive Director of State Emergency Management Agency (SEMA) in Anambra State, Mr Cyril Agupugo has directed shop owners affected by fire disaster at the Mgbuka Obosi Market to conduct integrity tests before rebuilding their burnt shops. Agupugo gave the directive when the panel set up on Mgbuka Obosi Market fire visited affected parts of the market. The executive director, who doubled as secretary of the panel, noted that it was wrong to start rebuilding shops and malls without integrity tests by the State Physical Planning Board and other relevant bodies. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network He said: “We all have to take proper measures before we commence rebuilding of shops. “I know that we are in a hurry to rebuild, to get back to our businesses, but we have to do the right thing first,’’ he advised.